  "text": "# Graceful Shutdown Signal Handling Across Go Services\n\n## Kubernetes Implementation\n\nKubernetes provides a comprehensive graceful shutdown mechanism across its services:\n\n### Signal Handler Registration\n- **kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/signal.go**: Core signal handler setup with `SetupSignalContext()` function that registers for SIGTERM and SIGINT using `signal.Notify()`. The handler uses a channel with buffer size 2 to allow catching two signals (first triggers graceful shutdown, second forces immediate exit).\n- **kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/signal_posix.go**: Platform-specific signal definitions registering both `os.Interrupt` and `syscall.SIGTERM` as shutdown signals.\n\n### Shutdown Timeout and Cleanup Ordering\n- **kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/genericapiserver.go**: The `RunWithContext()` function (lines 536-622) implements a sophisticated shutdown orchestration with lifecycle signals. It demonstrates proper cleanup ordering:\n  1. ShutdownInitiated - /readyz starts failing to drain load balancer traffic (ShutdownDelayDuration = 70s default)\n  2. AfterShutdownDelayDuration - HTTP server stops listening and begins graceful drain\n  3. NotAcceptingNewRequest - No new requests accepted, existing ones allowed to complete\n  4. InFlightRequestsDrained - All existing requests have completed (ShutdownTimeout = 60s default)\n  5. Audit backend shutdown - Only after requests are fully drained\n\n- **kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/lifecycle_signals.go**: Documents the complete shutdown sequence with precise timing. Multiple lifecycle events coordinate the graceful termination of request handling, connection draining, and component shutdown.\n\n- **kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/secure_serving.go** (lines 231-242): HTTP server graceful shutdown using `context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), shutDownTimeout)` before calling `server.Shutdown(ctx)